title: Saint Francis of Assisi's bones displayed for first time | 7NEWS
description: The skeletal remains of Saint Francis of Assisi are being publicly displayed for the first time to mark 800 years since the Christian friar's death. The Franciscan order is exhibiting the bones at their convent, where they anticipate at least 400,000 pilgrims will visit to pray. The remains will be available for public viewing for one month. title: Secret Service kills armed intruder at Mar-a-Lago | 7NEWS
description: The U.S. Secret Service shot and killed 21-year-old Austin Tucker Martin from North Carolina after he breached the security perimeter at Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago estate in Florida. Martin, who had been reported missing by his family, drove through a gate carrying a shotgun and jerry can of fuel, and raised the weapon at authorities before being fatally shot. Donald Trump was at the White House at the time of the incident, and investigators are searching for a motive while examining Martin's background. title: Regional GP shortages, Olympic mascot controversy and feline loyalty | 7NEWS
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce proposes barring city-based GPs from participating in Medicare unless they complete stints in regional areas to address chronic doctor shortages in rural Australia. The Canadian women's ice hockey team's viral reaction to receiving stuffed Olympic mascots at their medal ceremony sparks debate about sportsmanship and disappointment at the Winter Olympics. A study reveals cats are equally satisfied receiving comfort from strangers as from their owners, unlike dogs who seek reassurance specifically from their owners.
